Mobile Testing Suite
Domain: app-dev
Version: 1.0.0
Built by: Mobile QA Specialist (spawned by Styde Forge)

Stack:
- Detox: E2E for React Native (iOS + Android)
- Maestro: Flow-based mobile tests (iOS + Android)
- Appium: Cross-platform automation via WebDriverIO
- BrowserStack: Cloud device farm with App Automate
- Firebase Test Lab: Google device matrix testing
- GitHub Actions: CI orchestration with 4 workflows

Files:
  .detoxrc.js                    Detox config (iOS/Android, debug/release)
  e2e/jest.config.js             Jest runner for Detox
  e2e/auth-flow.test.js          Login, session, logout tests (20 cases)
  e2e/navigation-flow.test.js    Tab nav, deep links, gestures (10 cases)
  e2e/search-flow.test.js        Search, debounce, empty states (12 cases)
  e2e/offline-sync.test.js       Offline mode, sync queue, conflicts (10 cases)

  maestro/happy-path.yaml        Login to detail view flow
  maestro/validation-errors.yaml Form validation error states
  maestro/platform-native.yaml   Platform-specific gestures (iOS vs Android)
  maestro/search-results.yaml    Search with env vars + repeat blocks
  maestro/crud-flow.yaml         Create item with assertions
  maestro/config.json            Maestro test configuration

  appium/run-tests.js            Appium test runner (iOS + Android)
  appium/browserstack-tests.js   BrowserStack Appium integration
  appium/package.json            Appium/WebDriverIO dependencies

  firebase-test-lab/test-lab.yaml Device matrix config (Pixel 6/7, S23)
  firebase-test-lab/run.sh       Firebase upload + poll + download

  browserstack/run.sh            BrowserStack upload + trigger + poll

  ci/detox.yml                   Detox E2E in CI (iOS simulator + Android emulator)
  ci/maestro.yml                 Maestro flow runner (iOS + Android)
  ci/appium-farm.yml             Appium on BrowserStack + Firebase Test Lab
  ci/nightly-regression.yml      Nightly full regression (scheduled + manual)
  ci/pr-quality-gate.yml         PR gate: lint + build + maestro smoke

Secrets required (GitHub Actions):
  GCP_SA_KEY                  Firebase Test Lab service account
  FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID         GCP project ID
  BROWSERSTACK_USERNAME       BrowserStack account username
  BROWSERSTACK_ACCESS_KEY     BrowserStack account access key
  SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL           (optional) Nightly failure notifications

Commands (local):
  detox test -c android.emu.debug
  detox test -c ios.sim.debug
  maestro test maestro/happy-path.yaml
  cd appium && npm run appium:android

Runs spawned: 1 (run-20260626-001233)
